-- UN Carbon Plan Created $250 Billion in Investment, Official Says
-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 2012-10-31T03:32:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-31/un-carbon-plan-created-250-billion-in-investment-official-says.html
The United Nations carbon program
has generated about $250 billion in investment and is “not a
failure,” an official at the organization’s Framework
Convention on Climate Change said today in Bangkok.  “There is no oversupply in UN carbon credits,” said
Niclas Svenningsen, the manager for strategy and policy
development for the UNFCC said at a conference in the Thai
capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
